NAME
swocclient - manage client's 'Server Wait On Clients' flag.
SYNOPSIS
swocclient [OPTION]
DESCRIPTION
Sets, releases or reports on this client's 'Server Wait On Clients' flags on the
server.
OPTIONS
-h, --help  prints usage information.

-l, --lock  sets or increments the lock flag on the server.

-r, --release  releases or decrements the lock flag on the server.

-s, --status  reports on the status of server locking and how many locks are
held.

-V, --version  prints version information

-w, --wait  Wait until this client has 1 or fewer locks.
EXIT STATUS
0
if OK,

1
if minor problems,

64
error in command line arguments.
EXAMPLE
A simple example for the use of the wait option would be:-
.br
swocclient --lock ; swocclient --wait ; swocclient --release ; shutdown -P now
